Participation in the work of the University of Tartu folk dance ensemble, learning folk dance steps, learning different original dances, preparing for public performances (including learning basics of wearing folk clothing).Objectives/eesmärkid:  To enable students to participate in folk dance practice.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon successfully completing the course students: - know and can perform the essential steps in folk dance; - are familiar with the choreography of the dances in the group's repertoire; - are familiar with traditions of wearing Estonian folk clothing.
